# JavaScript Rules

## Namespace
Always attach code to the `theme` namespace to avoid global scope pollution:
```javascript
window.theme = window.theme || {};

theme.ComponentName = (() => {
  // private
  const init = (container) => { ... };
  const destroy = (container) => { ... };

  // public
  return { init, destroy };
})();
```

## Event Handling
- Always use `addEventListener` — never inline `onclick` or `href="javascript:"`
- Use `data-` attributes to pass values from Liquid to JS — never parse the DOM for text content
- Clean up event listeners when a section is removed (Shopify fires `shopify:section:unload`)

```javascript
// Bridge Liquid → JS via data attributes
// In Liquid:
// <div data-product-id="{{ product.id }}" data-section-type="product-recommendations">

// In JS:
const container = document.querySelector('[data-section-type="product-recommendations"]');
const productId = container?.dataset.productId;
```

## Shopify Section Events
Always handle Shopify theme editor events for live preview support:
```javascript
document.addEventListener('shopify:section:load', (e) => {
  const container = e.target;
  if (container.dataset.sectionType === 'your-section') {
    theme.YourSection.init(container);
  }
});

document.addEventListener('shopify:section:unload', (e) => {
  theme.YourSection.destroy(e.target);
});
```

## Fetch / Ajax
- Use the Shopify AJAX API for cart operations — never build cart URLs manually
- Always handle errors explicitly — don't let silent failures break the cart

```javascript
// Add to cart
const addToCart = async (variantId, quantity = 1) => {
  try {
    const res = await fetch('/cart/add.js', {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
      body: JSON.stringify({ id: variantId, quantity })
    });
    if (!res.ok) throw new Error('Add to cart failed');
    return await res.json();
  } catch (err) {
    console.error('[theme] Cart error:', err);
  }
};
```

## Performance
- Use `defer` on non-critical scripts
- Avoid `document.write()`
- Debounce scroll and resize handlers
- Use `IntersectionObserver` for lazy-loading components instead of scroll events

## Rules
- No jQuery unless the base theme already uses it
- No `var` — use `const` and `let` only
- Prefer `querySelectorAll` + `forEach` over older DOM methods
- Always guard against null: `const el = document.querySelector('...'); if (!el) return;`
